618
00:44:00,410 --> 00:44:02,250
♪And haven't moved on♪

619
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:10,930
Do you need anything else?

620
00:44:11,190 --> 00:44:12,230
I need that ketchup.

621
00:44:22,980 --> 00:44:24,310
And some soy sauce.

622
00:44:26,270 --> 00:44:27,430
Is the lid hot?

623
00:44:27,430 --> 00:44:28,460
Use this as a shield.

624
00:44:37,980 --> 00:44:38,830
I have done mine.

625
00:44:39,030 --> 00:44:40,030
I will get mine done soon.

626
00:44:45,290 --> 00:44:46,130
Do you need anything else?

627
00:44:46,450 --> 00:44:47,730
No, be careful not to burn yourself.

628
00:44:53,540 --> 00:44:54,540
Is this better now?

629
00:44:57,430 --> 00:44:58,020
Pretty good.

630
00:44:58,400 --> 00:44:59,420
It's not as sour anymore.

631
00:44:59,420 --> 00:45:00,530
The sauce you made is pretty good.

632
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:01,540
You can have this later.

633
00:45:01,570 --> 00:45:02,190
Okay, I'll eat.

634
00:45:02,390 --> 00:45:02,939
Okay.

635
00:45:18,750 --> 00:45:19,710
Wow, there's shrimp.

636
00:45:20,580 --> 00:45:21,390
It smells so good.

637
00:45:21,550 --> 00:45:22,230
The fish is here.

638
00:45:24,500 --> 00:45:25,350
The fish smells good.

639
00:45:25,350 --> 00:45:27,930
- Mr. Lu made both the shrimp and fish.
